Word Count: 700-1200, include author bio and author image 500x500px, article image 940x420px LINK EXCHANGE: You could add this link on this article of yours adding the sentence in yellow to this paragraph:

You should be able to create an atmosphere where employees feel less like someone is looking over their shoulders and feel free to explore their creativity. Don't micromanage your employee. Don't be overly controlling. Focus less on details and things that are going wrong. Focus more on things that are going well. Encourage your employees to explore things that are working and try to improve on them. Managers must be continuously growing to better help their employees, consider taking management training to be updated with the latest practices you can apply in your business. Your industry is one that always needs new game-changing ideas, and your employees have them. If they've worked in your restaurant for long, they sometimes even understand the customer needs better than you.
